Multi-region whole-genome sequencing data (median coverage ~100x) for the Set6 sample of the MSeq cohort, originally sequenced at lower resolution by Cross et al. (PMID 30177804). In this new version of the data (doi:10.1101/586560) we provide somatic single nucleotide variants, absolute clonal copy number segments and purity estimates.

Source: R/data_MSEQ_CRC_ADENOCARCINOMA_WGS.R
MSEQ_CRC_ADENOCARCINOMA_SET6.Rd

Multi-region whole-genome sequencing data (median coverage ~100x) for the Set6 sample of the MSeq cohort, originally sequenced at lower resolution by Cross et al. (PMID 30177804). In this new version of the data (doi:10.1101/586560) we provide somatic single nucleotide variants, absolute clonal copy number segments and purity estimates.

data(MSEQ_CRC_ADENOCARCINOMA_SET6)

Format

A list that contains a tibble with mutation, copy number and purity data.

References

G. Caravagna, T. Heide, M. Williams, L. Zapata, D. Nichol, K. Chkhaidze, W. Cross, G.D. Cresswell, B. Werner, A. Acar, C.P. Barnes, G. Sanguinetti, T.A. Graham, A. Sottoriva. Model-based tumor subclonal reconstruction. biorxiv 2019, doi:10.1101/586560

See also

Sample `MSEQ_CRC_ADENOCARCINOMA_SET7`.
